    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I mean it almost says</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\cong Fib(B)(\\underline -, P)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 298412008,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998536
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Compare with:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>h</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\cong Psh(B)(\\underline -, P)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>where now <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span> is a presheaf over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\underline -</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8667em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is Yoneda embedding</p>",
        "id": 298412194,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998602
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So maybe my question is ill-framed, since I should really consider <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mo>−</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B/-</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span> to land in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Fib(B)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, and then the answer becomes 'think of this as the Yoneda embedding for indexed categories'</p>",
        "id": 298412411,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998661
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact I'd bet a beer this <em>is</em> the Yoneda embedding for categories internal to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>S</mi><mi>e</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><msup><mi>B</mi><mrow><mi>o</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msup></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Set^{B^{op}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.88em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">t</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.88em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7385em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>... but this I can only eyeball</p>",
        "id": 298412628,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998743
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275932\">Matteo Capucci (he/him)</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/universality.20of.20the.20fundamental.20opindexed.20cat/near/298412008\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I mean it almost says</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\cong Fib(B)(\\underline -, P)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>Compare with:</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>h</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\cong Psh(B)(\\underline -, P)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">s</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">h</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>where now <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span> is a presheaf over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\underline -</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8667em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is Yoneda embedding</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span aria-label=\"face palm\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f926\" role=\"img\" title=\"face palm\">:face_palm:</span> these are the same exact statement, aren't they? Just on different sides of the Grothendieck construction</p>",
        "id": 298412886,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998816
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"275932\">Matteo Capucci (he/him)</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category-theory/topic/universality.20of.20the.20fundamental.20opindexed.20cat/near/298411332\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hence the statement reads</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>U</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≅</mo><mi>S</mi><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Fib(B)(U(S), P) \\cong Sp(B)(S, Fib(B)(\\underline -, P))</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">U</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">Sp</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span></span></span></span></span><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>But then I don't understand where splittings become relevant in all of this</p>",
        "id": 298413101,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1662998869
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The fibered YL extends the \"classical\" one from discrete fibrations to arbitrary fibrations. The role of splittings vanishes in the classical case since every discrete fibration has a unique one.</p>",
        "id": 298512608,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Schmude",
        "timestamp": 1663043817
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The equivalence <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi><mo>≅</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><munder accentunder=\"true\"><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">−</mo><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></munder><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P \\cong Fib(B)(\\underline{-}, P)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">≅</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0333em;vertical-align:-0.2833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord underline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.5833em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.7567em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"underline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">−</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2833em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> corresponds to the statement that the counit of the adjunction is an equivalence.</p>",
        "id": 298512802,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Schmude",
        "timestamp": 1663043984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 298545393,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1663061528
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you know if it's still true that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>b</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>B</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Fib(B)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ib</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is somehow generated by the fibrations <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mo>−</mo><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">B/- \\to B</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord\">−</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span></span></span></span>, like presheaves are always colimits of representables?</p>",
        "id": 298545481,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1663061571
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Presheaf categories are complete and cocomplete. Analogously, neither limits nor colimits should get you anything but discrete fibrations.<br>\nI don't know about other notions of \"generated by\", e.g. what's called a <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/separator\">[[separator]]</a> on the nlab.</p>",
        "id": 298584373,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Schmude",
        "timestamp": 1663075775
    }
]